body:
<!-- Demo: https://github.com/PaddlePaddle/PaddleNLP/pull/26 -->
### PR types
<!-- One of [ New features | Bug fixes | Function optimization | Performance optimization | Breaking changes | Others ] -->
Others
### PR changes
<!-- One of [ Models | APIs | Docs | Others ] -->
Models
### Description
<!-- Describe what this PR does -->

添加 BERT-base 模型在 IPU 上运行的支持, 包含 pretrainning 和 SQuAD 两个 task. 
模型使用静态图构建, 使用半精度训练 ,最终性能和精度运行结果如下:

| Task   | Metric   | Result  |
| ------ | -------- | ------- |
| Phase1 | MLM Loss | 1.6064  |
|        | NSP Loss | 0.0272  |
|        | MLM Acc  | 0.6689  |
|        | NSP Acc  | 0.9897  |
|        | tput     | 11700   |
| Phase2 | MLM Loss | 1.5029  |
|        | NSP Loss | 0.02444 |
|        | MLM Acc  | 0.68555 |
|        | NSP Acc  | 0.99121 |
|        | tput     | 3470    |
| SQuAD  | EM       | 79.9053 |
|        | F1       | 87.6396 |


全部的代码放在了 `examples/language_model/bert/static_ipu/` 目录下, 文件详情请参考 `README.md`

主要修改:

1. 为了实现在 IPU 上训练的最佳性能, 模型构图部分使用了自定义的 `modeling.py`

2. 添加了部分 ipu 的自定义算子用于构建模型(主要为了性能方面的考虑) 

3. 由于需要对模型的输入做 remask 操作, 使用单一线程载入数据集会导致数据载入耗时比较长, 影响 end2end 的 throughput, dataset 部分使用了自定义的dataloader, 使用了多个进程做 remask 操作, 见 `dataset_ipu.py`

4. `load_tf_ckpt.py` 用于映射 Google发布的 BERT pretrain weight https://storage.googleapis.com/bert_models/2018_10_18/uncased_L-12_H-768_A-12.zip

PR主要用于评估代码是否适合放在 paddlenlp 仓库中, 麻烦 reviewer 提出宝贵意见 😊

title: Add RoBERTa pretrain and finetune
body:
<!-- Demo: https://github.com/PaddlePaddle/PaddleNLP/pull/26 -->
### PR types
<!-- One of [ New features | Bug fixes | Function optimization | Performance optimization | Breaking changes | Others ] -->
New features
### PR changes
<!-- One of [ Models | APIs | Docs | Others ] -->
 Docs
### Description
<!-- Describe what this PR does -->
本项目是RoBERTa模型在 Paddle 2.0上的开源实现，包含了数据tokenization和预训练代码。本项目旨在用简练清晰的代码完成基本预训练任务（仅Masked Language Model）。该代码易于理解，便于修改和定制。


## 对比Hugging Face

Hugging Face[预训练代码](https://github.com/huggingface/transformers/tree/master/examples/pytorch/language-modeling)和本目录下run_pretrain_roberta.py对比如下：

### 参数环境
二者使用的数据、超参、GPU保持一致：

训练数据：wikipedia-en

学习率、训练步长等参数见上面 预训练 章节

训练GPU：Tesla V100 32G * 2

### 运行速度

| 6 eopch | Hugging Face | PaddleNLP |
|---------|--------------|--------|
| FP16    |     90 h     |  72 h  | 
| FP32    |     154 h    |  139 h | 

FP32精度下，PaddleNLP较Hugging Face快11%左右。
FP16混合精度下，PaddleNLP较Hugging Face快25%左右

### GLUE任务结果
总训练tokens：512(seq_len）* 32(batch_size) * 780000(iteration)，约RoBERTa训练量10%，在GLUE validation set表现：

| Model GLUE Score   | CoLA  | SST-2  | MRPC   | STS-B  | QQP    | MNLI   | QNLI   | RTE    |
|--------------------|-------|--------|--------|--------|--------|--------|--------|--------|
| RoBERTa paper      |  68.0 |  96.4  |  90.9  |  92.4  |  92.2  |  90.2  |  94.7  |  86.6  |
|Hugging Face 6-epoch| 36.6  | 89.6   | 87.7   | 85.8   | 88.7   | 80.3   | 88.8   | 54.2   |
| PaddleNLP 6-epoch  | 36.9  | 89.5   | 84.3   | 86.2   | 88.6   | 80.5   | 88.4   | 58.1   |

整体来说，PaddleNLP和Hugging Face在Masked Language Modeling预训练中表现相似，因训练量较小，结果比原paper普遍低10%。另外，MRPC和RTE数据集validation set较小，结果波动幅度比较大，故PaddleNLP和Hugging Face二者结果有一定diff。

body:
## Environment
```python
# python 3.8
paddlenlp                     2.1.1
paddlepaddle-gpu              2.0.2.post100
```

## Reproduction

```python
from paddlenlp.transformers.bert.tokenizer import  BertTokenizer
tokenizer = BertTokenizer.from_pretrained('bert-base-chinese')
text = '我喜欢中国[MASK]'

result = tokenizer.encode(text, truncation_strategy='tail', return_special_tokens_mask=True)
print(tokenizer.convert_ids_to_tokens(result['input_ids']))
print(tokenizer.all_special_tokens)
```

the output of above code is:
```shell
['[CLS]', '我', '喜', '欢', '中', '国', '[', '[UNK]', ']', '[SEP]']
['[SEP]', '[PAD]', '[CLS]', '[UNK]', '[MASK]']
```

so, it's abvious that it can't tokenize the special token in sentence. Why ？ How to handle it ??

***

btw, I check the [code](https://github.com/PaddlePaddle/PaddleNLP/blob/develop/examples/few_shot/pet/data.py#L76) from example dir, it replace the `<unk>` special token by hard way.  Is that the only way I can handle it ？

body:
<!-- Demo: https://github.com/PaddlePaddle/PaddleNLP/pull/26 -->
### PR types
<!-- One of [ New features | Bug fixes | Function optimization | Performance optimization | Breaking changes | Others ] -->
New features

### PR changes
<!-- One of [ Models | APIs | Docs | Others ] -->
Models
### Description
<!-- Describe what this PR does -->
- Add Ernie3 and FasterErnie3
- Add dygraph and inference demos and doc
- Use example (10B model can run on one A10-24G). For encrypted weight, we decrypt it only once instead of every forward step.

```python
import paddle
from paddlenlp.transformers import Ernie3Tokenizer, Ernie3ForGeneration

encrypted = True
paddle.set_default_dtype('float16')
tokenizer = Ernie3Tokenizer.from_pretrained(
    'ernie3-10b-confused' if encrypted else 'ernie3-10b')
x = tokenizer('中国的首都是哪里')
x = {k: paddle.to_tensor([v]) for k, v in x.items()}

model = Ernie3ForGeneration.from_pretrained(
    'ernie3-10b-confused' if encrypted else 'ernie3-10b',
    load_state_as_np=True)
output_ids, _ = model.generate(x['input_ids'],
                               eos_token_id=model.ernie3.end_token_id,
                               min_length=10,
                               max_length=20,
                               repetition_penalty=1.1,
                               temperature=0.9,
                               use_faster=True,
                               encrypted=encrypted,
                               use_fp16_decoding=True)
for idx, out in enumerate(output_ids.numpy()):
    seq = tokenizer.convert_ids_to_string(out)
    print(f'{idx}: {seq}')
```

- or the correct path to a directory containing relevant modeling files(model_weights and model_config).

Paddle的roberta-en-base的tokenizer，pad_token, mask_token等和原roberta模型不同（e.g. [PAD] vs <pad>），虽然pad_token_id相同，但可能会导致误解

title: FasterUnifiedTransformer/PLATO support dy2sta
body:
<!-- Demo: https://github.com/PaddlePaddle/PaddleNLP/pull/26 -->
### PR types
<!-- One of [ New features | Bug fixes | Function optimization | Performance optimization | Breaking changes | Others ] -->
Others

### PR changes
<!-- One of [ Models | APIs | Docs | Others ] -->
Models

### Description
<!-- Describe what this PR does -->
FasterUnifiedTransformer/PLATO support dy2sta. 
Provide Paddle Inference python script. 

#### NOTE:
There is a problem when using Paddle Inference python API. 

That is: 
First, it is necessary to call `load_op_meta_info_and_register_op()` to load custom op lib before `create_predictor()`. 
However, in `create_predictor()`, the same load operation will be processed again which leads to user-confused logs as follow: 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7160927/156274552-d1708e68-8712-45c4-b371-b7ade84b47ca.png)
If we do NOT call `load_op_meta_info_and_register_op()` first, then another exception which is `operator is not registered` will be throw. 

As for now, we can use `disable_glog_info()` to shut down all logs while the inference team may fix this within this year.
